						<summary>

						<p>Kadambavanēśvara temple, central shrine, south wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Madirai-koṇḍa Parakēsarivarman (Parāntaka I) Year 20.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records the gift of 90 sheep and a lamp-stand (<hi rend="italic">dharā-nilai-viḷakku</hi>) of 200 <hi rend="italic">palam</hi> weight to God Mahādēvar in Śiṟuttirukkōyil of Uṟṟumūr, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadānam</hi> in Vaḍakarai-Nalvayalūr-kkūṟṟam by Nīlakaṇṭaṉ Śāttaṉ, the <hi rend="italic">uḍaiyāṉ</hi> of the northern hamlet (<hi rend="italic">vaḍa-chēri</hi>) of this <hi rend="italic">ūr</hi> and the undertaking by the <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the place was to have a perpetual lamp burnt with one <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee, after taking over the sheep. </p>						

						</summary>
